  "prompt": "What can I do if my new CA driver's license hasn't come in the mail?",
  "response": "If your new California driver's license hasn't arrived in the mail after a reasonable amount of time, here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Check the Processing Timeline**:\n   - California DMV suggests that it can take up to 4-6 weeks for your new driver's license to arrive. Ensure that you have allowed for this standard processing time.\n\n2. **Confirm Your Address**:\n   - Ensure you provided the correct mailing address on your application. If there's a mistake, contact the DMV to update your address.\n\n3. **Check Status Online**:\n   - You can check the status of your driver's license application on the California DMV website.\n\n4. **Contact the DMV**:\n   - Call the California DMV directly to inquire about the status of your license. You can reach them at 1-800-777-0133.\n   - You might need to provide personal information and details about your application to receive specific updates.\n\n5. **Visit a DMV Office**:\n   - If you're not able to resolve the issue over the phone, consider visiting a local DMV office for assistance.\n\n6. **Temporary License**:\n   - If you need to drive urgently and your license has not arrived, inquire if you can get an interim or temporary license until your regular license arrives.\n\n7. **Check for Undelivered Mail**:\n   - Sometimes postal issues can cause delays. Check with your local post office to see if there might be any problems with mail delivery in your area.\n\n8. **Reapply**:\n   - If after contacting the DMV there are still issues, you may need to reapply for your driver's license. Be sure to discuss this option with the DMV to understand the process and any potential fees involved.\n\nTaking these steps should help you identify the problem and receive your new driver's license in a timely manner.",
